# Introduction to JavaScript
JavaScript is a versatile programming language that is primarily used for web development. It is a high-level, interpreted language that allows developers to create interactive and dynamic web pages. JavaScript can be used for both client-side(Browser, It is also work as compiler between the Browser and JavaScript) and server-side development, making it a popular choice for building web applications.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# History of JavaScript
JavaScript was created in 1995 by Brendan Eich while he was working at Netscape Communications Corporation. It was originally developed in just 10 days and was initially called Mocha, then renamed to LiveScript, and finally to JavaScript.

Mocha was the original name of the language, but it was changed to LiveScript to reflect its dynamic nature. 
Now it official name is EcmaScript, but it is commonly referred to as JavaScript.

